latestPosts.caption:
I can’t believe I’m even saying this out loud… we officially bought Huda Beauty BACK. This has been the craziest, most emotional ride of my life, and I’m honestly still processing it all. 

This moment is personal. It’s powerful. It’s the start of a whole new chapter, and I cannot WAIT to share this journey with you. Thank you for always being in our corner, for supporting us, and for believing in me since day one. We’re about to do things our way again… and it’s going to be EPIC.

Just a year after re-assuming her role as chief executive officer, @hudabeauty Beauty founder Huda Kattan ( @huda) is tacking on “owner” to her title, too.

The super influencer was among the first wave of beauty creators to parlay her digital audience into a beauty brand — and later made waves when TSG Consumer took a stake in the brand in 2017. 

Retail sales that year were said to be around $200 million, as reported.

Now, Kattan has purchased back that stake from the private equity firm. As reported, in August 2024, the brand had done north of $300 million in sales year-to-date, industry sources said at the time.

Kattan didn’t disclose terms of the deal, but did say she paid “a pretty penny” to assume outright ownership. Since regaining the CEO title, she’s also been hard at work on the brand’s next chapter, which has included a rebrand and a suite of products catering to previously untapped consumers.

“We went through such a transformation,” Kattan said of the brand’s trajectory. 

“We’ve been fully focused on that and getting things in order. The products have changed, the branding has changed, and we changed the way we speak to our community. Even internally, the way we’re doing things has really changed.”

Read more at WWD.com — #linkinbio

Report: @jamesmanso
